Visit to New York and the UN Assembly

We happen to have the opportunity to attend the 68th session of the United Nations General Assembly in New York. We stayed at NYU on the 32nd floor in the middle of Manhattan ! It was soon then that we became closer than ever. In late September, the mission arrived at Washington. During this mission, I was lucky to have the opportunity to speak at the Library of Congress, and have lunch with the US Special Representative for the African Union Soros Foundation .

On the afternoon of September 25 ,2013 we had the very immediate opportunity to attend the UN General Assembly, to witness the 9th President of the Republic of the Maldives Ibrahim Mohamed Solih , to read out his speech on behalf of the political technical delegation of the Maldives, as part of an observer of CSW56 at the UN in New York. We followed the general sessions every morning, including a special youth session with African youth leaders . I also had the opportunity to join a fact-finding mission at the Roxbury Community High School.
